{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''capillary''' (''plural'' '''capillaries''')

# {{anatomy}} Any of the small [[blood vessel]]s that connect [[arteriole]]s to [[venule]]s. Their walls are composed of a single layer of cells which allows [[molecule]]s such as [[oxygen]], water and [[lipid]]s to pass through them by diffusion and enter the tissues. Waste products such as [[carbon dioxide]] and [[urea]] can diffuse back into the blood to be carried away for removal from the body.

